      "\n  have h1 : M.encard = ν(G) := by\n    have h2 : M.encard = sSup {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} := by\n      have h3 : M.encard ∈ {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} := by\n        refine' ⟨M, h.1, rfl⟩\n      have h4 : ∀ n, n ∈ {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} → n ≤ M.encard := by\n        intro n hn\n        rcases hn with ⟨M', hM', hn⟩\n        have h5 : M'.encard ≤ M.encard := h.2 M' hM'\n        linarith\n      rw [sSup_eq_iff]\n      constructor\n      · -- Show that M.encard is in the set\n        exact h3\n      · -- Show that M.encard is minimal among upper bounds\n        intro n hn\n        have h6 : n ∈ {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} := hn\n        have h7 : n ≤ M.encard := h4 n h6\n        linarith\n    rw [h2]\n    all_goals simp [ν]\n  exact h1",
      "\n  have h1 : M.encard ≤ ν(G) := by\n    apply le_csSup\n    refine ⟨M, h.1, rfl⟩\n  have h2 : ν(G) ≤ M.encard := by\n    have h3 : ∀ n, (∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ n = M.encard) → n ≤ M.encard := by\n      intro n hn\n      rcases hn with ⟨M', hM', hn⟩\n      have h4 : M'.encard ≤ M.encard := h.2 M' hM'\n      linarith [hn, h4]\n    have h4 : ν(G) = sSup {n | ∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ n = M.encard} := by rfl\n    rw [h4]\n    apply csSup_le\n    intro n hn\n    have h5 : n ≤ M.encard := h3 n hn\n    linarith\n  linarith [h1, h2]",
      "\n  have h1 : G.IsMatching M := h.toIsMatching\n  have h2 : ∀ M', G.IsMatching M' → M'.encard ≤ M.encard := by\n    intro M' hM'\n    exact h.max hM'\n```\n\nNow we need to prove `M.encard = ν(G)`. We'll do this by showing both inequalities.\n\n```tactics\nhave h3 : M.encard ≤ ν(G) := by\n  have h4 : M.encard ∈ {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} := by\n    refine ⟨M, h1, rfl⟩\n  have h5 : M.encard ≤ sSup {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} := by\n    apply Set.mem_sSup_le\n    exact h4\n  rw [show ν(G) = sSup {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} by rfl] at *\n  all_goals linarith\n```\n\nNext, we prove `ν(G) ≤ M.encard`.\n\n```tactics\nhave h6 : ν(G) ≤ M.encard := by\n  have h7 : ν(G) = sSup {n | ∃ M', G.IsMatching M' ∧ n = M'.encard} := by rfl\n  rw [h7]\n  apply sSup_le\n  intro n hn\n  rcases hn with ⟨M', hM', hn⟩\n  have h8 : M'.encard ≤ M.encard := h2 M' hM'\n  linarith [hn, h8]\n```\n\nFinally, we can conclude `M.encard = ν(G)` using the two inequalities.\n\n```tactics\nlinarith [h3, h6]\n```\n\nThis completes the proof of `IsMaxMatching.encard`.\n</think>\n```lean\nimport Mathlib.Data.Set.Cardinal\nimport Mathlib.Data.SSup\nimport Mathlib.Order.Lattice.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Order.SSup.Basic\n\nimport Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Group.Finset\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Degree\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Max\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Augmenting\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Pfaffian\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Degree\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Locally\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Neighbor\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Walk\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Lift\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Lift.Lemmas\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Lift.Card\nimport Mathlib.Data.Graph.Matching.Tutte.Lift.Lemmas\nimp